61 template <typename T>
62 inline bool getParam(const std::string& param, T& val)
63 {
64  // first look within private namespace
65  ros::NodeHandle pnh("~");
66  if (pnh.getParam(param, val))
67  return true;
68 
69  // then in local namespace
70  ros::NodeHandle nh;
71  return nh.getParam(param, val);
72 }

74 // As loading of parameters is quite slow, we share them across all tests
75 class SharedData
76 {
77  friend class KinematicsTest;
78  typedef pluginlib::ClassLoader<kinematics::KinematicsBase> KinematicsLoader;
79 
80  moveit::core::RobotModelPtr robot_model_;
81  std::unique_ptr<KinematicsLoader> kinematics_loader_;
82  std::string root_link_;
83  std::string tip_link_;
84  std::string group_name_;
85  std::vector<std::string> joints_;
86  std::vector<double> seed_;
87  std::vector<double> consistency_limits_;
88  double timeout_;
89  double tolerance_;
90  int num_fk_tests_;
91  int num_ik_cb_tests_;
92  int num_ik_tests_;
93  int num_ik_multiple_tests_;
94  int num_nearest_ik_tests_;
95 
96  SharedData(SharedData const&) = delete; // this is a singleton
97  SharedData()
98  {
99  initialize();
100  }
101 
102  void initialize()
103  {
104  ROS_INFO_STREAM("Loading robot model from " << ros::this_node::getNamespace() << "/" << ROBOT_DESCRIPTION_PARAM);
105  // load robot model
106  rdf_loader::RDFLoader rdf_loader(ROBOT_DESCRIPTION_PARAM);
107  robot_model_ = std::make_shared<moveit::core::RobotModel>(rdf_loader.getURDF(), rdf_loader.getSRDF());
108  ASSERT_TRUE(bool(robot_model_)) << "Failed to load robot model";
109 
110  // init ClassLoader
111  kinematics_loader_ = std::make_unique<KinematicsLoader>("moveit_core", "kinematics::KinematicsBase");
112  ASSERT_TRUE(bool(kinematics_loader_)) << "Failed to instantiate ClassLoader";
113 
114  // load parameters
115  ASSERT_TRUE(getParam("group", group_name_));
116  ASSERT_TRUE(getParam("tip_link", tip_link_));
117  ASSERT_TRUE(getParam("root_link", root_link_));
118  ASSERT_TRUE(getParam("joint_names", joints_));
119  getParam("seed", seed_);
120  ASSERT_TRUE(seed_.empty() || seed_.size() == joints_.size());
121  getParam("consistency_limits", consistency_limits_);
122  if (!getParam("ik_timeout", timeout_) || timeout_ < 0.0)
123  timeout_ = 1.0;
124  if (!getParam("tolerance", tolerance_) || tolerance_ < 0.0)
125  tolerance_ = DEFAULT_TOLERANCE;
126  ASSERT_TRUE(consistency_limits_.empty() || consistency_limits_.size() == joints_.size());
127  ASSERT_TRUE(getParam("num_fk_tests", num_fk_tests_));
128  ASSERT_TRUE(getParam("num_ik_cb_tests", num_ik_cb_tests_));
129  ASSERT_TRUE(getParam("num_ik_tests", num_ik_tests_));
130  ASSERT_TRUE(getParam("num_ik_multiple_tests", num_ik_multiple_tests_));
131  ASSERT_TRUE(getParam("num_nearest_ik_tests", num_nearest_ik_tests_));
132 
133  ASSERT_TRUE(robot_model_->hasJointModelGroup(group_name_));
134  ASSERT_TRUE(robot_model_->hasLinkModel(root_link_));
135  ASSERT_TRUE(robot_model_->hasLinkModel(tip_link_));
136  }
137 
138 public:
139  auto createUniqueInstance(const std::string& name) const
140  {
141  return kinematics_loader_->createUniqueInstance(name);
142  }
143 
144  static const SharedData& instance()
145  {
146  static SharedData instance;
147  return instance;
148  }
149  static void release()
150  {
151  SharedData& shared = const_cast<SharedData&>(instance());
152  shared.kinematics_loader_.reset();
153  }

205 public:
206  testing::AssertionResult isNear(const char* expr1, const char* expr2, const char* /*abs_error_expr*/,
207  const geometry_msgs::Point& val1, const geometry_msgs::Point& val2, double abs_error)
208  {
209  // clang-format off
210  if (std::fabs(val1.x - val2.x) <= abs_error &&
211  std::fabs(val1.y - val2.y) <= abs_error &&
212  std::fabs(val1.z - val2.z) <= abs_error)
213  return testing::AssertionSuccess();
214 
215  return testing::AssertionFailure()
216  << std::setprecision(std::numeric_limits<double>::digits10 + 2)
217  << "Expected: " << expr1 << " [" << val1.x << ", " << val1.y << ", " << val1.z << "]\n"
218  << "Actual: " << expr2 << " [" << val2.x << ", " << val2.y << ", " << val2.z << "]";
219  // clang-format on
220  }
221  testing::AssertionResult isNear(const char* expr1, const char* expr2, const char* /*abs_error_expr*/,
222  const geometry_msgs::Quaternion& val1, const geometry_msgs::Quaternion& val2,
223  double abs_error)
224  {
225  if ((std::fabs(val1.x - val2.x) <= abs_error && std::fabs(val1.y - val2.y) <= abs_error &&
226  std::fabs(val1.z - val2.z) <= abs_error && std::fabs(val1.w - val2.w) <= abs_error) ||
227  (std::fabs(val1.x + val2.x) <= abs_error && std::fabs(val1.y + val2.y) <= abs_error &&
228  std::fabs(val1.z + val2.z) <= abs_error && std::fabs(val1.w + val2.w) <= abs_error))
229  return testing::AssertionSuccess();
230 
231  // clang-format off
232  return testing::AssertionFailure()
233  << std::setprecision(std::numeric_limits<double>::digits10 + 2)
234  << "Expected: " << expr1 << " [" << val1.w << ", " << val1.x << ", " << val1.y << ", " << val1.z << "]\n"
235  << "Actual: " << expr2 << " [" << val2.w << ", " << val2.x << ", " << val2.y << ", " << val2.z << "]";
236  // clang-format on
237  }
238  testing::AssertionResult expectNearHelper(const char* expr1, const char* expr2, const char* abs_error_expr,
239  const std::vector<geometry_msgs::Pose>& val1,
240  const std::vector<geometry_msgs::Pose>& val2, double abs_error)
241  {
242  if (val1.size() != val2.size())
243  return testing::AssertionFailure() << "Different vector sizes"
244  << "\nExpected: " << expr1 << " (" << val1.size() << ")"
245  << "\nActual: " << expr2 << " (" << val2.size() << ")";
246 
247  for (size_t i = 0; i < val1.size(); ++i)
248  {
249  ::std::stringstream ss;
250  ss << "[" << i << "].position";
251  GTEST_ASSERT_(isNear((expr1 + ss.str()).c_str(), (expr2 + ss.str()).c_str(), abs_error_expr, val1[i].position,
252  val2[i].position, abs_error),
253  GTEST_NONFATAL_FAILURE_);
254 
255  ss.str("");
256  ss << "[" << i << "].orientation";
257  GTEST_ASSERT_(isNear((expr1 + ss.str()).c_str(), (expr2 + ss.str()).c_str(), abs_error_expr, val1[i].orientation,
258  val2[i].orientation, abs_error),
259  GTEST_NONFATAL_FAILURE_);
260  }
261  return testing::AssertionSuccess();
262  }

264  void searchIKCallback(const geometry_msgs::Pose& /*ik_pose*/, const std::vector<double>& joint_state,
265  moveit_msgs::MoveItErrorCodes& error_code)
266  {
267  std::vector<std::string> link_names = { tip_link_ };
268  std::vector<geometry_msgs::Pose> poses;
269  if (!kinematics_solver_->getPositionFK(link_names, joint_state, poses))
270  {
271  error_code.val = error_code.PLANNING_FAILED;
272  return;
273  }
274 
275  EXPECT_GT(poses[0].position.z, 0.0f);
276  if (poses[0].position.z > 0.0)
277  error_code.val = error_code.SUCCESS;
278  else
279  error_code.val = error_code.PLANNING_FAILED;
280  }

302 #define EXPECT_NEAR_POSES(lhs, rhs, near) \
303  SCOPED_TRACE("EXPECT_NEAR_POSES(" #lhs ", " #rhs ")"); \
304  GTEST_ASSERT_(expectNearHelper(#lhs, #rhs, #near, lhs, rhs, near), GTEST_NONFATAL_FAILURE_);

306 TEST_F(KinematicsTest, getFK)
307 {
308  std::vector<double> joints(kinematics_solver_->getJointNames().size(), 0.0);
309  const std::vector<std::string>& tip_frames = kinematics_solver_->getTipFrames();
310  moveit::core::RobotState robot_state(robot_model_);
311  robot_state.setToDefaultValues();
312 
313  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < num_fk_tests_; ++i)
314  {
315  robot_state.setToRandomPositions(jmg_, this->rng_);
316  robot_state.copyJointGroupPositions(jmg_, joints);
317  std::vector<geometry_msgs::Pose> fk_poses;
318  EXPECT_TRUE(kinematics_solver_->getPositionFK(tip_frames, joints, fk_poses));
319 
320  robot_state.updateLinkTransforms();
321  std::vector<geometry_msgs::Pose> model_poses;
322  model_poses.reserve(tip_frames.size());
323  for (const auto& tip : tip_frames)
324  model_poses.emplace_back(tf2::toMsg(robot_state.getGlobalLinkTransform(tip)));
325  EXPECT_NEAR_POSES(model_poses, fk_poses, tolerance_);
326  }
327 }

329 // perform random walk in joint-space, reaching poses via IK
330 TEST_F(KinematicsTest, randomWalkIK)
331 {
332  std::vector<double> seed, goal, solution;
333  const std::vector<std::string>& tip_frames = kinematics_solver_->getTipFrames();
334  moveit::core::RobotState robot_state(robot_model_);
335  robot_state.setToDefaultValues();
336 
337  if (!seed_.empty())
338  robot_state.setJointGroupPositions(jmg_, seed_);
339 
340  bool publish_trajectory = false;
341  getParam<bool>("publish_trajectory", publish_trajectory);
342  moveit_msgs::DisplayTrajectory msg;
343  msg.model_id = robot_model_->getName();
344  moveit::core::robotStateToRobotStateMsg(robot_state, msg.trajectory_start);
345  msg.trajectory.resize(1);
346  robot_trajectory::RobotTrajectory traj(robot_model_, jmg_);
347 
348  unsigned int failures = 0;
349  static constexpr double NEAR_JOINT = 0.1;
350  const std::vector<double> consistency_limits(jmg_->getVariableCount(), 1.05 * NEAR_JOINT);
351  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < num_ik_tests_; ++i)
352  {
353  // remember previous pose
354  robot_state.copyJointGroupPositions(jmg_, seed);
355  // sample a new pose nearby
356  robot_state.setToRandomPositionsNearBy(jmg_, robot_state, NEAR_JOINT);
357  // get joints of new pose
358  robot_state.copyJointGroupPositions(jmg_, goal);
359  // compute target tip_frames
360  std::vector<geometry_msgs::Pose> poses;
361  ASSERT_TRUE(kinematics_solver_->getPositionFK(tip_frames, goal, poses));
362 
363  // compute IK
364  moveit_msgs::MoveItErrorCodes error_code;
365  kinematics_solver_->searchPositionIK(poses[0], seed, 0.1, consistency_limits, solution, error_code);
366  if (error_code.val != error_code.SUCCESS)
367  {
368  ++failures;
369  continue;
370  }
371 
372  // on success: validate reached poses
373  std::vector<geometry_msgs::Pose> reached_poses;
374  kinematics_solver_->getPositionFK(tip_frames, solution, reached_poses);
375  EXPECT_NEAR_POSES(poses, reached_poses, tolerance_);
376 
377  // validate closeness of solution pose to goal
378  auto diff = Eigen::Map<Eigen::ArrayXd>(solution.data(), solution.size()) -
379  Eigen::Map<Eigen::ArrayXd>(goal.data(), goal.size());
380  if (!diff.isZero(1.05 * NEAR_JOINT))
381  {
382  ++failures;
383  ROS_WARN_STREAM("jump in [" << i << "]: " << diff.transpose());
384  }
385 
386  // update robot state to found pose
387  robot_state.setJointGroupPositions(jmg_, solution);
388  traj.addSuffixWayPoint(robot_state, 0.1);
389  }
390  EXPECT_LE(failures, (1.0 - EXPECTED_SUCCESS_RATE) * num_ik_tests_);
391 
392  if (publish_trajectory)
393  {
394  ros::NodeHandle nh;
395  ros::AsyncSpinner spinner(1);
396  spinner.start();
397  ros::Publisher pub = nh.advertise<moveit_msgs::DisplayTrajectory>("display_random_walk", 1, true);
398  traj.getRobotTrajectoryMsg(msg.trajectory[0]);
399  pub.publish(msg);
400  ros::WallDuration(0.1).sleep();
401  }
402 }

404 static double parseDouble(XmlRpc::XmlRpcValue& v)
405 {
406  if (v.getType() == XmlRpc::XmlRpcValue::TypeDouble)
407  return static_cast<double>(v);
408  else if (v.getType() == XmlRpc::XmlRpcValue::TypeInt)
409  return static_cast<int>(v);
410  else
411  return 0.0;
412 }
413 static void parseVector(XmlRpc::XmlRpcValue& vec, std::vector<double>& values, size_t num = 0)
414 {
415  ASSERT_EQ(vec.getType(), XmlRpc::XmlRpcValue::TypeArray);
416  if (num != 0)
417  {
418  ASSERT_EQ(static_cast<size_t>(vec.size()), num);
419  }
420  values.reserve(vec.size());
421  values.clear();
422  for (int i = 0; i < vec.size(); ++i) // NOLINT(modernize-loop-convert)
423  values.push_back(parseDouble(vec[i]));
424 }
425 static bool parseGoal(const std::string& name, XmlRpc::XmlRpcValue& value, Eigen::Isometry3d& goal, std::string& desc)
426 {
427  std::ostringstream oss;
428  std::vector<double> vec;
429  if (name == "pose")
430  {
431  parseVector(value["orientation"], vec, 4);
432  Eigen::Quaterniond q(vec[3], vec[0], vec[1], vec[2]); // w x y z
433  goal = q;
434  parseVector(value["position"], vec, 3);
435  goal.translation() = Eigen::Map<Eigen::Vector3d>(vec.data());
436  oss << name << " " << goal.translation().transpose() << " " << q.vec().transpose() << " " << q.w();
437  desc = oss.str();
438  return true;
439  }
440  for (unsigned char axis = 0; axis < 3; ++axis)
441  {
442  char axis_char = 'x' + axis;
443  // position offset
444  if (name == (std::string("pos.") + axis_char))
445  {
446  goal.translation()[axis] += parseDouble(value);
447  desc = name + " " + std::to_string(parseDouble(value));
448  return true;
449  }
450  // rotation offset
451  else if (name == (std::string("rot.") + axis_char))
452  {
453  goal *= Eigen::AngleAxisd(parseDouble(value), Eigen::Vector3d::Unit(axis));
454  desc = name + " " + std::to_string(parseDouble(value));
455  return true;
456  }
457  }
458  return false;
459 }

461 TEST_F(KinematicsTest, unitIK)
462 {
463  XmlRpc::XmlRpcValue tests;
464  if (!getParam("unit_tests", tests))
465  return;
466 
467  std::vector<double> seed, sol;
468  const std::vector<std::string>& tip_frames = kinematics_solver_->getTipFrames();
469  moveit::core::RobotState robot_state(robot_model_);
470  robot_state.setToDefaultValues();
471 
472  // initial joint pose from seed_ or defaults
473  if (!seed_.empty())
474  robot_state.setJointGroupPositions(jmg_, seed_);
475  robot_state.copyJointGroupPositions(jmg_, seed);
476 
477  // compute initial end-effector pose
478  std::vector<geometry_msgs::Pose> poses;
479  ASSERT_TRUE(kinematics_solver_->getPositionFK(tip_frames, seed, poses));
480  Eigen::Isometry3d initial, goal;
481  tf2::fromMsg(poses[0], initial);
482 
483  auto validate_ik = [&](const geometry_msgs::Pose& goal, std::vector<double>& truth) {
484  // compute IK
485  moveit_msgs::MoveItErrorCodes error_code;
486  kinematics_solver_->searchPositionIK(goal, seed, timeout_,
487  const_cast<const std::vector<double>&>(consistency_limits_), sol, error_code);
488  ASSERT_EQ(error_code.val, error_code.SUCCESS);
489 
490  // validate reached poses
491  std::vector<geometry_msgs::Pose> reached_poses;
492  kinematics_solver_->getPositionFK(tip_frames, sol, reached_poses);
493  EXPECT_NEAR_POSES({ goal }, reached_poses, tolerance_);
494 
495  // validate ground truth
496  if (!truth.empty())
497  {
498  ASSERT_EQ(truth.size(), sol.size()) << "Invalid size of ground truth joints vector";
499  Eigen::Map<Eigen::ArrayXd> solution(sol.data(), sol.size());
500  Eigen::Map<Eigen::ArrayXd> ground_truth(truth.data(), truth.size());
501  EXPECT_TRUE(solution.isApprox(ground_truth, 10 * tolerance_)) << solution.transpose() << std::endl
502  << ground_truth.transpose() << std::endl;
503  }
504  };
505 
506  ASSERT_EQ(tests.getType(), XmlRpc::XmlRpcValue::TypeArray);
507  std::vector<double> ground_truth;
508 
509  /* process tests definitions on parameter server of the form
510  - pos.x: +0.1
511  joints: [0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0]
512  - pos.y: -0.1
513  joints: [0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0]
514  */
515  for (int i = 0; i < tests.size(); ++i) // NOLINT(modernize-loop-convert)
516  {
517  goal = initial; // reset goal to initial
518  ground_truth.clear();
519 
520  ASSERT_EQ(tests[i].getType(), XmlRpc::XmlRpcValue::TypeStruct);
521  std::string desc;
522  for (std::pair<const std::string, XmlRpc::XmlRpcValue>& member : tests[i])
523  {
524  if (member.first == "joints")
525  parseVector(member.second, ground_truth);
526  else if (!parseGoal(member.first, member.second, goal, desc))
527  ROS_WARN_STREAM("unknown unit_tests' key: " << member.first);
528  }
529  {
530  SCOPED_TRACE(desc);
531  validate_ik(tf2::toMsg(goal), ground_truth);
532  }
533  }
534 }

536 TEST_F(KinematicsTest, searchIK)
537 {
538  std::vector<double> seed, fk_values, solution;
539  moveit_msgs::MoveItErrorCodes error_code;
540  solution.resize(kinematics_solver_->getJointNames().size(), 0.0);
541  const std::vector<std::string>& fk_names = kinematics_solver_->getTipFrames();
542  moveit::core::RobotState robot_state(robot_model_);
543  robot_state.setToDefaultValues();
544 
545  unsigned int success = 0;
546  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < num_ik_tests_; ++i)
547  {
548  seed.resize(kinematics_solver_->getJointNames().size(), 0.0);
549  fk_values.resize(kinematics_solver_->getJointNames().size(), 0.0);
550  robot_state.setToRandomPositions(jmg_, this->rng_);
551  robot_state.copyJointGroupPositions(jmg_, fk_values);

678 // validate that getPositionIK() retrieves closest solution to seed
679 TEST_F(KinematicsTest, getNearestIKSolution)
680 {
681  std::vector<std::vector<double>> solutions;
682  kinematics::KinematicsQueryOptions options;
683  kinematics::KinematicsResult result;
684 
685  std::vector<double> seed, fk_values, solution;
686  moveit_msgs::MoveItErrorCodes error_code;
687  const std::vector<std::string>& fk_names = kinematics_solver_->getTipFrames();
688  moveit::core::RobotState robot_state(robot_model_);
689  robot_state.setToDefaultValues();
690 
691  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < num_nearest_ik_tests_; ++i)
692  {
693  robot_state.setToRandomPositions(jmg_, this->rng_);
694  robot_state.copyJointGroupPositions(jmg_, fk_values);
695  std::vector<geometry_msgs::Pose> poses;
696  ASSERT_TRUE(kinematics_solver_->getPositionFK(fk_names, fk_values, poses));
697 
698  // sample seed vector
699  robot_state.setToRandomPositions(jmg_, this->rng_);
700  robot_state.copyJointGroupPositions(jmg_, seed);
701 
702  // getPositionIK for single solution
703  kinematics_solver_->getPositionIK(poses[0], seed, solution, error_code);
704 
705  // check if getPositionIK call for single solution returns solution
706  if (error_code.val != error_code.SUCCESS)
707  continue;
708 
709  const Eigen::Map<const Eigen::VectorXd> seed_eigen(seed.data(), seed.size());
710  double error_get_ik =
711  (Eigen::Map<const Eigen::VectorXd>(solution.data(), solution.size()) - seed_eigen).array().abs().sum();
712 
713  // getPositionIK for multiple solutions
714  solutions.clear();
715  kinematics_solver_->getPositionIK(poses, seed, solutions, result, options);
716 
717  // check if getPositionIK call for multiple solutions returns solution
718  EXPECT_EQ(result.kinematic_error, kinematics::KinematicErrors::OK)
719  << "Multiple solution call failed, while single solution call succeeded";
720  if (result.kinematic_error != kinematics::KinematicErrors::OK)
721  continue;
722 
723  double smallest_error_multiple_ik = std::numeric_limits<double>::max();
724  for (const auto& s : solutions)
725  {
726  double error_multiple_ik =
727  (Eigen::Map<const Eigen::VectorXd>(s.data(), s.size()) - seed_eigen).array().abs().sum();
728  if (error_multiple_ik <= smallest_error_multiple_ik)
729  smallest_error_multiple_ik = error_multiple_ik;
730  }
731  EXPECT_NEAR(smallest_error_multiple_ik, error_get_ik, tolerance_);
732  }
733 }
